**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ul√∏nnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her p√• Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi s√∏ger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: ‚Äú**Spildt M√¶lk**‚Äù I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  m√∏der vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afh√¶ngighed af m√¶lk vender op og ned p√• hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig h√•rd for en s√• tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at g√∏re det endnu v√¶rre s√• har han en afh√¶ngighed til m√¶lk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne l√¶re folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet s√• form√•r han n√¶rmest altid at f√• et allerede nyt akavet m√∏de til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil v√¶re forplejning p√• set, men jobbet er ul√∏nnet.

vedh√¶ftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud p√• i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretr√¶kker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt M√¶lk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

Es erwartet Dich ein Mix aus √úbungen und Improszenen, damit Du lernst Deinen Impulsen zu vertrauen und an Deiner Durchl√§ssigkeit und Wahrhaftigkeit zu arbeiten. Ich schaffe einen sicheren und gesch√ºtzen Raum, in dem Du Dich ausprobieren kannst. Mir ist es wichtig, die FLINTA* Community zu st√§rken und freue mich, wenn diese immer weiter w√§chst.

items.text:
**Hello to all the actors, aspiring actors, and curious creatives out there‚Äî this one‚Äôs for you!**

 

I‚Äôm a Berlin-based director and teacher launching a small actor training space called **Studio LeBolt**, and I‚Äôm offering **a 2-day** **monologue workshop in English** this September.

 

It‚Äôs a supportive space for anyone ‚Äî beginner or experienced ‚Äî looking to reconnect with acting, build confidence, and develop a strong audition-ready piece. Whether you‚Äôre returning to performance, building your showreel, or just want to explore something new‚Äî you‚Äôre welcome.

 

My work is rooted in embodiment, presence, and, most of all, play. I‚Äôd love for you to join us!

 

**info + registration:**

dates: September 6 & 13 (13:00‚Äì17:00)

**Early bird sign up only until Aug. 14**

location: Treptower Park (Park Studio)

register: stephanielebolt.com/studio-lebolt

 

 

Happy to answer any questions or send more details ‚Äî and would be grateful if you passed it on to someone who might be looking for something like this.

Stephanie xo

items.text:
üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Student Short Film (UNPAID)

Production Title: Baggage

Role: Protagonist ‚Äì Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th ‚Äì 19th September

Location: Berlin

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

üìß If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)‚Äì kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)‚Äì ahadg8@gmail.com

Casting call ¬∑ 04.10 ¬∑ 14:00‚Äì16:00 ¬∑ Krak√≥w

When and where: October 4, 14:00‚Äì16:00, Krak√≥w, Romanowicza 19b. 

The project: student independent short film, prepared for submission to European festivals and media exposure.
Plot: action takes place 30 years from our time; a dystopia about the "oppression" of the body and rebellion against a repressive regime.
Who do you work with: a professional team led by director
What the artists will get: promotion in our social networks, the opportunity to use filmed materials in the portfolio, visibility at European festivals.
The film is independent - payment for shifts is not provided, agreement on commissions in case of success of the film and awards.
Organizer: Theatre studio "Bez Uprzedze≈Ñ" (NIP 6793287079).
Filming: 2‚Äì3 shifts in the window of October 15‚Äì31, 2025 (exact dates to be confirmed).

We are careful about the topic of the film and the boundaries of the artists: any sensitive actions (for example, a kiss) - only with your express consent, under safe conditions. No nudity without separate agreement. There is zero tolerance for harassment and discrimination on the site. 

Who are we looking for?
The main roles:
- Female, 20‚Äì30 years old. Height 160‚Äì175, clothing size S‚ÄìM. Natural European appearance, feminine. Blonde/brown/light shoulder-length hair or longer, straight or wavy. The eyes are light or light brown. Fluent  English required
- Male, 20‚Äì30 years old. Height 178‚Äì195, athletic physique (natural dramatik appearance). Short dark blond or dark hair, straight or with a slight wave. No beard or with light facial hair. Fluent  English required
- Male, 25‚Äì40 years old. Slender, possible androgynous type. An expressive gaze and mimics, large eyes, dark haired. Preferably clean shaven. Visible tattoos/piercings are allowed (moderately).

Episodes / Cameos:
- Woman, 20‚Äì35 years old. Height 165‚Äì180, "dramatic" type: expressive green or dark brown eyes, full lips, dark/black hair.
- Dancers (4 performers): Women with good plasticity; the ability to improvise to club music solo and in interaction.
Group of club visitors (5 performers):
- 3 men 30‚Äì50 ‚Äî strong physique, pronounced natural hair is allowed.
- 2 women 20‚Äì30 ‚Äî short, slender, elegant constitution.
- male couple (2 performers), comfortable with interaction on the camera, including a screen kiss (with your consent).
A couple with a performative BDSM image (2 performers):
- The dominant figure - tall, large; any age/gender; comfortable wearing heels/platform shoes.
- Submissive partner - possible representation in latex and a mask (including a stylized one). Only with full consent, without dangerous practices; closed playground; interactions are agreed in advance.
- A girl with pronounced aesthetic modifications. For example: enlarged breasts, thick false eyelashes, voluminous lips.
- Passers-by on the street, M/F, different types and ages

For participating in casting please fill in the form:

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I‚Äôm a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I‚Äôm looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I‚Äôm not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I‚Äôm eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I‚Äôm excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I‚Äôm incredibly proud of them.

I‚Äôm looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK‚Äôs vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I‚Äôm actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

AMERIVENTS is Hiring!

We‚Äôre excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click ‚ÄúApply‚Äù (mention ‚ÄúCORE-NYC‚Äù in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules‚Äîyou choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

CASTING CALL - PRESENTER FOR SOCIAL MEDIA CAMPAIGN FOR FINANCIAL SERVICES COMPANY IN LONDON (POTENTIALLY 13th OCTOBER)

Hi all, we‚Äôre currently casting for a presenter for a short social media video with us. We‚Äôre looking for someone with experience presenting, who can share links for us to review.

We‚Äôre hoping for someone with bags of personality who‚Äôs happy and confident to approach people in the street and stoke up a conversation, but you‚Äôll also be required to deliver a piece to camera. You‚Äôd need to be very confident riding a bike and have a decent level of fitness, as we‚Äôll be following you cycle around London for a couple of hours on a branded bike.

Please only send on details if you have Presenting experience, with links to recent work. Email details to casting@feral-films.com. Please do not DM me, only send details via email.

This is a paid role, with travel (to and from the location within London) and sustenance all covered on the shoot.

The shoot date is pencilled for the 13th October, this may change however. The location is likely to be Central London. 

Thank you!

items.text:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

items.summary:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ul√∏nnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her p√• Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi s√∏ger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: ‚Äú**Spildt M√¶lk**‚Äù I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  m√∏der vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afh√¶ngighed af m√¶lk vender op og ned p√• hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig h√•rd for en s√• tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at g√∏re det endnu v√¶rre s√• har han en afh√¶ngighed til m√¶lk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne l√¶re folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet s√• form√•r han n√¶rmest altid at f√• et allerede nyt akavet m√∏de til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil v√¶re forplejning p√• set, men jobbet er ul√∏nnet.

vedh√¶ftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud p√• i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretr√¶kker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt M√¶lk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

der vil v√¶re forplejning p√• set, men jobbet er ul√∏nnet.

üìå If you have applied during the book opening period you will be notified whether successful or not but please bear with us as we work through applications

regarding applications

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12‚Äì19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18‚Äì28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25‚Äì40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty ‚Äî a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

items.text:
üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Student Short Film

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

Anyone wanna check out CiveVita? We are proud to be partners with our neighbors on Campus here at Hollywood Park!

Thursday, October 9
Friday, October 10
Sunday, October 12

Step into Tarantino Live: Pulp Rock Extravaganza‚Äîa cinematic rock concert reimagined inside one of the most breathtaking live venues in the world. Staged within CineVita, the largest Belgian Spiegeltent ever built, this immersive experience transforms a night out into a red-carpet-worthy escape. With 3,000 mirrors, hand-cut stained glass, and wood-carved detailing‚Äîall handcrafted by fourth-generation artisans‚ÄîCineVita is more than a venue. Fueled by the unforgettable soundtracks of Quentin Tarantino‚Äôs films and brought to life by a world-class cast of singers, musicians, and immersive performers, Tarantino Live is a high-octane celebration of music, story, and style.

**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambiti√∏se og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en r√¶kke skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske f√¶tter hj√¶lper ham med at flytte, m√• han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud ‚Äì men om at turde definere sine egne gr√¶nser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke s√¶rlig bem√¶rkelsesv√¶rdig
* har sv√¶rt ved at s√¶tte gr√¶nser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 √•r
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* K√òN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ul√∏nnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail p√• sara774g@gmail.som med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

**It's all about pure acting: playing the theme!**
***Secure your place and the early bird price until 15 October.***

3 x online workshops and 2 x individual coaching sessions with Christine Schmalor.

*‚ÄúIn my many years of practice, I have found that most actors have no problem portraying realistic characters, but are lost when it comes to abstraction. Yet this is exactly what contemporary dramaturgy demands. This means we have to develop a different acting consciousness with new techniques.‚Äù*

Welcome to the experiment of transforming your stage presence!

[https://online-theatre-academy.com/play-theme/](https://online-theatre-academy.com/play-theme/)

The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Elizabeth Line Station / Free Parking)

Unpaid charity production

If you think you can step in and save the show then please get in touch asap - email casting@brooksidetheatre.com or PM me

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

#castingcall #casting #addamsfamilymusical #musicaltheatre #stage #stageshow

üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I‚Äôve been training with Steve Eastin and it‚Äôs honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You‚Äôve seen this guy, he‚Äôs in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he‚Äôs teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just‚Ä¶ different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It‚Äôs not gonna be for everyone but if you‚Äôre someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you‚Äôre just along for the ride, this is that.

It‚Äôs rooted in Charles Conrad‚Äôs whole ‚Äúchoiceless awareness‚Äù thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure ‚Äúbeats‚Äù land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you‚Äôre curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything‚Äôs filmed so you‚Äôre used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They‚Äôre small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn‚Äôt still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it‚Äôs a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Banbury, Oxfordshire | ¬£250 for 2 days + travel considered

We‚Äôre casting for the final scenes of Failsafe, a psychological short film currently in production with a professional crew.

Directed by Rob Hutt ‚Äî award-winning filmmaker of Time Spent (23 awards, 22 nominations, 8.8 IMDb rating). You can view Rob‚Äôs IMDb profile here:
üëâ https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4254248/?ref_=ext_shr_lnk

This project is already generating festival momentum and will be featured in Pro Movie Maker Magazine.

ROLE:
 ‚Ä¢ Female, playing age 25‚Äì35
 ‚Ä¢ Character: A game designer whose reality begins to fracture, blurring with the world she created. Performance requires range: strength, vulnerability, psychological depth.

DETAILS:
 ‚Ä¢ ¬£250 for 2 days filming.
 ‚Ä¢ Shoot will take place across one Saturday & Sunday, back-to-back.
 ‚Ä¢ Filming must be completed on one of the following weekends:
 ‚Ä¢ 11‚Äì12 October 2025
 ‚Ä¢ 18‚Äì19 October 2025
 ‚Ä¢ 25‚Äì26 October 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Banbury, Oxfordshire. Reasonable travel costs considered.
 ‚Ä¢ Short film ‚Äî to be submitted to national and international film festivals.
 ‚Ä¢ Professional set with full crew.
 ‚Ä¢ Self-tape auditions required.

üì© To apply / receive the self-tape brief:
https://www.starnow.com/casting/failsafe-3020838/female-games-designer-5368483/ or DM directly.

‚ú® This is a chance to be part of a powerful, festival-ready film with proven pedigree.

So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran‚Äôs Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann‚Äôs Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro‚Äôs Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane‚Äôs costumes for years! 

https://2025screamfest.eventive.org/films/68d1b14f6ac811912ea77b5c?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAR6Vy5trrNroF8v33cSuHpp_m2mf0qAtnnMljE9_T7BIh64lBOdHCOJWfuCTlQ_aem_eM-d05jAN52my1WjOr_zoQ

***CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM!!!***

***UNPAID & NON-UNION***

Location: Vancouver, BC

Film Dates: November 14th, 15th, & 16th with 2 rehearsals to be scheduled after casting

Casting "Confession", a student short film set in the late 1950s about a closeted devout Catholic who confesses his secret love for his priest during confession, only to discover the priest feels the same way.

Father Elias D'Arcy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic priest who has been the head of Jacob‚Äôs church for a few years now, developing a close relationship with his parish. He came from a poor family, the child of Irish immigrants and the eldest of 6, he‚Äôs always had a nurturing nature to him and often helped others to the detriment of his own mental capacity. A closeted homosexual, Elias has delved deep into his religion and joined the priesthood to stave off any romantic connection, unwilling to come to terms with his sexuality.

Jacob McCarthy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic and closeted gay man, his struggles with his raised religion and his sexuality being the catalyst for his story. He forced himself to marry a girl he was raised going to church with to promote a sense of normalcy and to please his family as the eldest child and only son expected to carry on the family name and reputation. He's unhappy with the life he chose to live for other people, feeling as though no one really knows him for who he truly is.

Actors will be compensated with a copy of the film, credit, and a meal every day of filming.

For audition scheduling and sides, please contact a.culp@infocusfilmschool.com

CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that‚Äôs left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided as well as top billing credits and IMDB credit.

üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Student Short Film

Production Title: Baggage

Director: Kole Jackson 

Role: Protagonist ‚Äì Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th ‚Äì 19th September

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk
